 Step 1: Create IAM Role for API Gateway Logging

Go to IAM → Roles → Create Role.
Trusted entity type: Select AWS Service.
Choose API Gateway as the service.
Attach the managed policy: AmazonAPIGatewayPushToCloudWatchLogs
create it.

Step 2: Set Role ARN in API Gateway Account Settings

Go to API Gateway → Settings (not the API or stage settings).
Under CloudWatch log role ARN, paste the ARN of the IAM role you created.

Step 3: Enable CloudWatch Logs for API Gateway

Select the API you want to monitor.
In the left navigation pane, click Stages.
Choose the stage (e.g., dev, prod) where you want to enable logging.
Scroll down to Logs/Tracing section.
Enable CloudWatch Logs:

Check Enable CloudWatch Logs.
Select Log level:

ERROR → Logs only errors.
INFO → Logs request and response data.
DEBUG → Logs full details (use carefully in production).

Click Save Changes.

Step 4: Verify CloudWatch Logs

Go to CloudWatch → Logs → Log groups.
You should see a log group named: API-Gateway-Execution-Logs_{API-ID}/{Stage-Name}


Ref : https://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/set-up-logging.html#apigateway-cloudwatch-log-formats

Use a real route (recommended) --> To trigger some logs, you can invoke your API using curl or any HTTP client:

curl -i -X POST \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{}' \
  https://<api-id>.execute-api.<region>.amazonaws.com/<stage>/path

To verify that logging is enabled and working correctly, you can perform the following steps:

aws apigatewayv2 get-stages --api-id <API_ID> ----> Replace <API_ID> with your actual API ID. This command will return the stage details, including the logging configuration.

View Log Streams

aws logs describe-log-streams \
  --log-group-name /aws/apigateway/<API_ID> \
  --order-by LastEventTime \
  --descending

Replace <API_ID> with your actual API ID. This command will list the log streams in the specified log group, ordered by the time of the last event.

Read Logs (invoke must happen first!)

aws logs get-log-events \
  --log-group-name /aws/apigateway/<API_ID> \
  --log-stream-name <LOG_STREAM_NAME>

Replace <API_ID> with your actual API ID and <LOG_STREAM_NAME> with the name of the log stream you want to read. This command will retrieve the log events from the specified log stream.